version_description: Complete chords and well aligned / breaks indicated / downward movement at the end of verses / capo information for studio and officially released live versions.
A vert different way of playing this song for a much fuller presentation, for those who prefer to play this way, like I do.
This version has the chords for each measure to help the beginner on this song.
In this version I added an intro, changed the key and made some other changes in the chords. I think this one is more acurate than the other one. Cheers

song_name: Weve Got A Groovy Thing Goin

version_description: Easy to read and play for the beginners.
My version is fully tabbed and has the full lyrics. The chords are placed in the correct timing.

I tried to stick as much as possible to the power chords (fifths) used by Survivor in his original version : it gives the song all its power. I then switch to classic full chords during the major part of the chorus. I figured out it sounds a lot better this way. Enjoy.

Acoustic campfire version with little tricks. Instead of the fifths in intro you can use just Am, G, Em, F. In the verse I like to play F and G with A-bass (it is C with the capo), but can be played without those. F/A = X03211. G/A = X05433.
